<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Verant supports the PvP server</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?TheBlack">TheBlack</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 2:35 p.m. 4/5/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Verant supports the PvP server<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=2019" TARGET=_self>Re: You Have Got to be Kidding</A> (Destruc -AoD-)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>

<BR>Good point. That was just one of the problems that the PvP server faced over the past couple months that Brad/Verant has solved for us. Currently they are working on fixing the DOT issue. Brad McQuaid wants this server to be successful, and they are willing to put the time in (within reason) to help assure this.
<P>Granted overhauling the combat system at this point is probably out of the question, but if we can identify key problem areas that can be tweaked or adjusted without requiring major code rewrites then it is entirely possible that Verant will be able to help us out. The further along the game gets however, the less development time I suspect Verant will have to apply to Everquest (as their team will need to ramp up on EQ2).
<P>So if there are specific short comings that can be nailed down in the PvP system, by all means state them here for everyone to comment on. If they are valid concerns and appear to be issues that could be resolved without major overhaul then they can be brought up with Verant.
<P>As for the pure fighters, I don't know if anything can be done to make them competitive 1 on 1 with the rest of the classes. Access to limited SoTW abilities, better bows, and flurry attacks are a few possible ideas to help fighters. They are however design enhancements, not fixes for glaring shortcomings or bugs.
<P>Perhaps some of our PvP players with more experience playing fighters can comment on this particular problem area?
<P>&gt; you say verant will do nothing to change anything on the pvp
<BR>&gt; server cause 90% of the people are on non-pvp they why did they
<BR>&gt; make it that looting corpses that were killed my monsters
<BR>&gt; unlootable? does this affect the 90% of people? obviously verant
<BR>&gt; is listening to its pvp shard and who ever said anything about
<BR>&gt; changing the whole battle system to balance pvp there are other
<BR>&gt; ways to balance it then just changeing the battle system
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
